OL,7,FSir Lindsay's decision to upend
OL,8,Fparliamentary convention by selecting
OL,9,Fa Labour amendment to an SNP motion
OL,10,Fcalling for an immediate ceasefire in
OL,11,Fthe Israel-Hamas war, which meant the
OL,12,FScottish Nationalists never got a
OL,13,Fchance to vote on their opposition
OL,14,Fday, drew fierce criticism and calls
OL,15,Ffor his resignation.
OL,17,FThe Speaker issued multiple apologies
OL,18,Ffor his "mistake" as he emphasised
OL,19,Fconcerns over the security of MPs who
OL,20,Fhave faced threats over their stance
OL,21,Fon the conflict.
